  <prompt>
    Round out Wave 1 test coverage with ~5 error-path tests in AiCompletionNodeExecutorTests.cs covering:
    Validate() error messages (FR-13 contract), missing-prompt fast-fail, malformed JSON response from LLM,
    LLM HTTP error wrapping, and cancellation propagation. After this task, AiCompletionNodeExecutor line
    coverage must be &gt;85% per NFR-05 — measure and report.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET test author. Error paths are the failure modes that block production rollout — every error
    code the executor can return must have a deterministic test. Mock IOpenAiClient to throw / return
    malformed responses; assert NodeOutput.Error carries the right NodeErrorCodes value + an actionable
    message.
  </role>

  <goal>
    AiCompletionNodeExecutorTests.cs extended with ~5 tests:
    1. Validate_Fails_WhenActionFkMissing — context with null Action → NodeValidationResult.Failure with FR-13 message
    2. Validate_Fails_WhenToolPresent — context with Tool populated → Failure with "AiCompletion node MUST NOT have a Tool" message
    3. ExecuteAsync_ReturnsError_WhenLlmReturnsMalformedJson — mock IOpenAiClient returns invalid JSON → NodeOutput.Error with InvalidResponse-equivalent code
    4. ExecuteAsync_ReturnsError_WhenLlmThrowsHttpException — mock throws HttpRequestException → NodeOutput.Error with LlmCallFailed-equivalent code; original exception message visible in the error
    5. ExecuteAsync_PropagatesCancellation_WhenTokenCancelled — pre-cancelled CancellationToken → either OperationCanceledException OR NodeOutput.Error with Cancelled code (mirror AiAnalysisNodeExecutor pattern)
    Coverage target: AiCompletionNodeExecutor &gt;85% line coverage after this task (NFR-05). Measure and report.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="executor-under-test">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/AiCompletionNodeExecutor.cs</file>
    <file purpose="existing-test-file">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Nodes/AiCompletionNodeExecutorTests.cs</file>
    <file purpose="sibling-error-tests">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Nodes/AiAnalysisNodeExecutorTests.cs</file>
    <file purpose="error-codes">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/NodeErrorCodes.cs</file>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="adr-038">docs/adr/ADR-038-testing-strategy.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-038">Testing Strategy — integration-heavy pyramid. Mock at executor boundary. NO Mock&lt;HttpMessageHandler&gt;.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-13">Validate() error messages must match the literal wording from task 005 (UI displays verbatim). Tests assert message text.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-14">Tests cover error paths (missing prompt, malformed JSON, LLM error).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-05">Coverage target: &gt;85% line coverage for AiCompletionNodeExecutor. This is the closing task — must reach the threshold.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §8 TEST-MODIFYING">Override row — testing tag triggers FULL rigor unconditionally.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md §F">Test update obligation — this task closes the FR-12 + FR-13 + FR-14 test obligation for Wave 1.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-038 §7 build-vs-maintain">Error-path tests are MAINTAIN-class — they verify the error contract surfaced to consumers (UI / orchestrator / logs).</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>testing/xunit-bff-pattern</topic>
    <files>
