  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL · 📋 REASON: TEST-MODIFYING override (tag testing + tests/** modification per CLAUDE.md §8 override row — FULL rigor UNCONDITIONAL per ADR-038). Quality gates Step 9.5 required · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md FR-13 + FR-14 + NFR-05 + ADR-038 + the existing AiCompletionNodeExecutorTests.cs from tasks 007/008.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Read NodeErrorCodes class">
      Confirm the named codes available: InvalidResponse, LlmCallFailed, Cancelled, InternalError, ValidationFailed (or equivalents). Tests assert against these names.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Read AiAnalysisNodeExecutor error tests as reference">
      Note: how malformed-JSON / HTTP-exception / cancellation tests are shaped. Mirror exactly for AiCompletion.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Add 5 error-path tests">
      Append to AiCompletionNodeExecutorTests.cs:
      1. Validate_Fails_WhenActionFkMissing — assert error message text matches FR-13 contract from task 005
      2. Validate_Fails_WhenToolPresent — assert error message text matches
      3. ExecuteAsync_ReturnsError_WhenLlmReturnsMalformedJson — _openAiClient.Setup returns invalid JSON; assert NodeOutput.Error.Code == InvalidResponse-equivalent
      4. ExecuteAsync_ReturnsError_WhenLlmThrowsHttpException — _openAiClient.Setup throws HttpRequestException; assert NodeOutput.Error.Code == LlmCallFailed-equivalent; assert original exception message appears in the wrapped error message
      5. ExecuteAsync_PropagatesCancellation_WhenTokenCancelled — pre-cancelled token; either OperationCanceledException propagates OR NodeOutput.Error with Cancelled code (whichever matches AiAnalysisNodeExecutor pattern)
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Run tests">
      Run: dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Nodes/AiCompletionNodeExecutorTests.cs
      Expect: 15-17 total tests passing (5-7 from 007 + 5 from 008 + 5 from 009).
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Measure coverage — MUST exceed 85%">
      Run: dotnet test --collect:"XPlat Code Coverage" scoped to AiCompletionNodeExecutor.
      ASSERT: line coverage &gt; 85%. If &lt; 85%, add additional targeted tests for uncovered branches. Document final coverage % in task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify acceptance">
      Re-read the 5 added tests. Confirm: each error code path tested + message text matches FR-13 contract + no ADR-038 banned patterns.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `/code-review` on the modified test file. Run `/adr-check` against ADR-038. Run `/test-diet` preview — confirm tests classify as MAINTAIN.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 009 status complete; advance current-task.md (009 unblocks 010).
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Commit">
      Commit AiCompletionNodeExecutorTests.cs change with conventional message.
      Example: test(bff/r7): error-path tests + &gt;85% coverage gate (Wave 1 task 009, FR-13, FR-14, NFR-05)
    </step>
  </steps>

